g.aria-label: A giant cloud of gas and dust, called a nebula, began to collapse in upon itself due to gravity.
This resulted in the formation of a protoplanetary disk of gas and dust. At the centre, where the temperature and pressure were greatest, a protostar was formed, which eventually grew into our Sun.
Material left behind by the developing Sun clumped together to form larger and larger objects. These clumps swept up most of the material within their orbits and became planets.
